International Holding Capital Corp. said it agreed to be bought by Maruwa Koyo Co. of Japan for $28.50 a share, or $31.2 million. 

The thrift-holding company reported earlier this month that it was negotiating with an undisclosed potential buyer.
International Holding said terms call for Maruwa to purchase 121,000 of the shares, about 10% of International's stock, within 30 days. 

In over-the-counter trading Friday, International Holding closed at $24, up $2.50. 

